news.title: Gurugram civic body fines two societies for flouting waste management rules
news.para: The corporation has given 20 days to ensure compliance with SWM rules, otherwise, it will initiate further action. The regulations mandate that the waste generators have to treat their wet waste and recycle their dry waste.

news.title: DLF appoints Mahender Singh as independent director
news.para: In a regulatory filing, the company informed that the board of directors approved, the appointment of Mahender Singh as an independent director for a period of five consecutive years with effect from August 7, 2024.

news.title: Sand dredged from rivers to be allowed to tackle shortfall: Goa environment minister
news.para: Minister Aleixo Sequeira announced the preparation of a draft khazan land management plan to be opened for public suggestions. The marina project remains shelved due to a high court stay order. The government plans dredging rivers for sand and aims to regularize fishermen's houses under CRZ provisions.

news.title: Average sale price in residential segment to grow 5-6% in FY25: ICRA
news.para: The rating agency expects the area sold in the top seven cities in India to increase by 10-12 per cent to 785-800 million square feet in 2024-25. These seven cities are Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Pune, Kolkata, and Chennai

news.title: China Evergrande Group's liquidators file lawsuit against PwC in Hong Kong
news.para: The lawsuit is part of an ongoing effort to recover creditors' investments after a Hong Kong court in January ordered the liquidation of Evergrande, once China's biggest real estate company.

news.title: House prices in Britain rise by 2.3% in July: Halifax data
news.para: House prices increased by an annual 2.3%, the biggest yearly increase since January. The last time prices rose by more on an annual basis was February 2023 when they rose by 2.5%.

news.title: Delhi HC appoints arbitrator to deal with disputes between Yuvraj Singh, Brilliant Etoile
news.para: ​The high court said the arbitration would take place under the aegis of the Delhi International Arbitration Centre (DIAC) and would abide by its rules and regulations.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace leases 42,000 sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: It plans to expand its managed office space portfolio by an additional one million sq ft space during the current financial year. It has already added two to three properties as part of this plan.

news.title: GIS mapping of properties is invading privacy: Panaji corporators
news.para: The corporators alleged that officials participating in this activity are persuading residents to allow the mappers inside homes. The officials are presenting a letter from the Corporation of the City of Panaji (CCP) and asserting that they have been authorised by the corporators to carry out this task, the corporation members said at the CCP meeting held on Tuesday.

news.title: Mysuru builders to meet Karnataka CM over stuck project approvals
news.para: The last meeting was held in September 2023, and its significance lies in the fact that it grants approval for layout projects, the release of sites in developed layouts, and khatha transfers. Despite conducting meetings for other purposes, Muda has not cleared files, subjecting developers to considerable hardships, according to the stakeholders.

news.title: Stilt-plus-four floors policy rolled out again despite ongoing case: Plea in Haryana HC
news.para: The Punjab and Haryana High Court heard a plea against the construction of stilt-plus-four floors in Gurgaon's residential areas. The government assured the court that it would halt further approvals until the next hearing on August 22. An expert committee had been appointed to review this policy, which had been contested by the Gurgaon Citizens Council since 2021.

news.title: Indirapuram's handover to Ghaziabad civic body may happen in August 2024
news.para: The GDA board, which met in Meerut on Monday, gave its in-principle approval to the cost estimates drawn up following a joint survey by the corporation and GDA. Divisional commissioner Selva Kumari J, who was presiding over the meeting, has asked GDA vice-chairperson Atul Vats and civic commissioner Vikramaditya Singh Malik to fix the date of transfer within two weeks.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to raze 29 bungalows along Indrayani river
news.para: Tanaji Gambhire, a local environmental activist, had moved the NGT against the project River Villa, claiming that the bungalows were constructed within the blue line, area adjacent to a riverbank where development activities are not allowed

news.title: No prima facie offence of cheating against Kamala Mills owner: Judge
news.para: The judge observed it cannot be said Gowani had an intention to cheat when he entered into a deed of conveyance with the complainant to buy a plot.

news.title: DDA meeting chaired by LG takes key decisions on three housing schemes
news.para: DDA announced that the Sasta Ghar Housing Scheme 2024 would offer low-income group (LIG) and Economically Weaker Section (EWS) flats at discounted rates in Ramgarh Colony, Siraspur, Loknayakpuram, Rohini, and Narela through first come first serve (FCFS) mode.

news.title: Centre refuses to grant 'metro' status to Bengaluru
news.para: ​​For the four designated metropolitan cities, 50% of the salary was considered for computing the exemption limits under section 10(13A). However, for other cities, including Bengaluru, this limit has been set at 40%.

news.title: Mumbai: Government plans SRA buildings on 65% of SDZ, not 80%
news.para: While it sounds like good news for Mumbai, citizens' activists cautioned that any construction on saltpan and mangrove land would only spell a disaster for the city.

news.title: Mumbai: Ghatkopar police books four partners of Punjalal G Dave Realtors LLP
news.para: ​Maulik Dave, one of the directors of Dave Realtors, has refuted all the allegations levelled in the FIR and said that instead, the complainant, Sanjay Dhawan, has to pay them a huge amount.

news.title: IDFC First Bank leases four floors in Oberoi Commerz III in Mumbai
news.para: The rentals for nearly 1.65 lakh sq ft office space in commercial tower Oberoi Commerz III, part of larger layout Oberoi Garden City, is set at Rs 233 per sq ft a month.

news.title: Government gives option to calculate LTCG tax on properties, pay lower tax
news.para: As per the amendments to Finance Bill, 2024, circulated to the Lok Sabha members on Tuesday, individuals or HuF who bought houses before July 23, 2024, can compute his/her taxes under the new scheme [@12.5 per cent without indexation] and old scheme [@20 per cent with indexation] and pay such tax which is lower of the two.
